abstract: Ohio Gov John R Kasich is emphasizing his position as centrist Midwesterner with productive governing record and intent to attack partisan gridlock in his bid for 2016 Republican presidential nomination; must overcome his unfamiliarity to many voters in race dominated by household names.
lead_paragraph: Gov. John R. Kasich of Ohio hopes his pragmatic, can-do appeal in New Hampshire will help propel him from his current low standing in the polls.

headline.main: John Kasich Looks to Stand Out From Bigger Names in 2016 Race
headline.print_headline: Ohio Governor Looks to Stand Out From Bigger Names
